1.title: The New Gold Rush

episode of.title: Million Dollar Listing San Francisco (TV Series 2015)

1.plot: Three ambitious brokers-by-the-bay, Justin Fichelson, Andrew Greenwell and Roh Habibi, strive to outsell one another in a cutthroat market filled by demanding young tech clients. Andrew is a real estate veteran who has tackled nearly every challenge in his career...except for predicting the mistakes of a co-lister in an affluent suburb. Justin is a native San Franciscan who knows the city inside and out, but runs up against a tough client who wants more than Justin's tech network may be willing to spend. 2.title: Remember the Alamo Listing

episode of.title: Million Dollar Listing San Francisco (TV Series 2015)

2.plot: With his new listing in the Mission still under construction, Justin has to try and sell the neighborhood before he can sell the house. Roh's business partner Joel criticizes his open house and demands a more conventional approach. Meanwhile, Andrew is dealing with an emotional seller and an inexperienced co-lister....and he's not sure which is more problematic.

3.title: When You Wish Upon a Starchitecht

episode of.title: Million Dollar Listing San Francisco (TV Series 2015)

3.plot: Andrew lands a listing in an up-and-coming neighborhood. Justin's property is finally finished and ready to show, but the size of the backyard proves to be a difficult selling point. Roh scores a listing by making promises that may be impossible to keep.

4.title: Fights in Bernal Heights

episode of.title: Million Dollar Listing San Francisco (TV Series 2015)

4.plot: Roh finally manages to track down the architect of his new listing and now has to sell the penthouse. Justin takes a listing with his dentist. Andrew's quest to find his clients a property in an up-and-coming neighborhood takes an unexpected turn.

5.title: We'll Always Have Paris...

episode of.title: Million Dollar Listing San Francisco (TV Series 2015)

5.plot: Justin's client Stephanie is an old friend, who he hopes might turn into something more if he can make the sale. Andrew has his hands full with a neurotic client. Roh takes a co-listing in the Marina with a colleague.

6.title: We Are the Chammy-ions

episode of.title: Million Dollar Listing San Francisco (TV Series 2015)

6.plot: Justin takes a listing with an old friend, but quickly realizes that mixing business with his personal life is not a good combination. Andrew snags an amazing winery estate, and now just needs to pair it with the right buyer. Roh's newest listing has everything an agent could want.

7.title: Carry On, Hayward Son

episode of.title: Million Dollar Listing San Francisco (TV Series 2015)

7.plot: Andrew takes a listing just outside of the city, but trying to get a bidding war started is never pleasant...even in Pleasanton. Justin struggles to find a buyer for his demanding client, Kevin, who expects someone to drastically overpay for his place. Luckily for Justin, Roh pays a visit with a potential client.

8.title: St. Louie Blues

episode of.title: Million Dollar Listing San Francisco (TV Series 2015)

8.plot: Andrew takes the biggest listing of his entire life, but in order to sell it, he's going to have to work side-by-side with the seller's very opinionated son. Roh snags a listing in Potrero Hill, but quickly realizes that sometimes business can be a very personal journey. Justin lands a hundred-year old firehouse that's been converted into a condo.

9.title: I Don't Have Time for This, Tiny Man!

episode of.title: Million Dollar Listing San Francisco (TV Series 2015)

9.plot: In the season finale, Roh and Justin continue to disagree at the open house and the negotiating table. In Tiburon, Andrew's in jeopardy of losing the biggest listing of his career, so he has to play nice, something that doesn't come easy for him.

imdb.plot outline: The fourth addition to the successful franchise, "Million Dollar Listing: San Francisco" follows the lives of three ambitious, hot shot real estate agents as they strive to outsell one another, listing some of the most expensive and architecturally diverse properties in America. These brokers-by-the-bay are pushed to the limit by demanding clients, intense competition and complicated personal lives.
